sense.name: make coincide in time or operation
sense.examples: This program will synchronize your PC's internal clock with one of the several atomic clocks maintained by the United States. Interesting to note that he synchronized his camera with his watch. He synchronized his breathing with hers to increase the proximity. She synchronized in the next step the approvals from the downstream wsus server and the full wsus content. Agreement should synchronize actions with African Union - Security Council.

sense.name: make (motion picture) sound simultaneous with the action
sense.examples: Lewis is rumored to have been the first to have synchronized Pink Floyd's Dark Side of the Moon with the movie The Wizard of Oz. Some of his most famous works are called 'Shorts', in which he synchronized animation to the music.
